    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-04-01T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-04-01T14:00:00-05:00" n="441"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d441">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.48 Refugees/2500: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-04-01T20:00:00+01:00"
                            >April 1, 1941—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received April 1—5:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1266. The Polish Ambassador has requested the British Foreign Office to take up
                    with the Intergovernmental Committee the possibility of extending the
                    Committee’s scope to cover Polish refugees. Winterton, Emerson, Snow of the
                    Foreign Office, and Achilles discussed the matter this morning. It was agreed
                    that the scope of the Committee could be extended only with the agreement of all
                    member Governments and that it would be useless and inadvisable even to
                    communicate the Polish proposal to them at the present time. The Foreign Office
                    is advising the Ambassador that the foregoing is the considered view of the
                    Chairman.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
